pros:
Innovative and fast-paced (can be a negative too at times as it can be stressful);

Learning from colleagues;

Career development

cons:
Cut-throat in certain departments - your position may be cut short due to bad Management and illegal workforce practices, without warnings or any written documentation;

Some executives having inappropriate sexual relations with employees and favoring them yet rest of Management turn a blind eye;

Robbing Peter to pay Paul culture - in order to award an employee, funds need to be taken from other employees and it leads to a competitive culture where most employees are brown-nosing Management for their upcoming bonus/stock payout and trying to out-do their peers.
